<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,1414,1585]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1450,1476]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Sinclair, F. &amp; Hearn, J. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z." box="[323,595,1450,1477]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref52592" refString="Schweger, S., Melika, G., Tang, C. - T., Yang, M. - M., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Sinclair, F., Hearn, J., Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z. (2015 b) New species of cynipid inquilines of the genus Saphonecrus (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) from the Eastern Palaearctic, with a re-appraisal of known species world-wide. Zootaxa, 4054 (1), 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4054.1.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Schwéger 
<emphasis box="[441,492,1450,1476]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al</emphasis>
. (2015b)
</bibRefCitation>
established the new combination indirectly after synonymizing the monospecific genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nieves-Aldrey &amp; Butterill" authorityYear="2014" box="[318,452,1486,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Lithonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[318,452,1486,1512]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Lithonecrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang, Melika &amp; Bozso" authorityYear="2013" box="[515,716,1486,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Lithosaphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[515,716,1486,1512]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Lithosaphonecrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,1414,1585]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1522,1548]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Biology.</emphasis>
Reared from bud petiole and leaf galls on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Miq.) Rehder (Nieves-Aldrey &amp; Butterill 2014)" authorityName="Rehder (Nieves-Aldrey &amp; Butterill" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Lithocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="celebicus">
<emphasis box="[763,1008,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Lithocarpus celebicus</emphasis>
(Miq.) Rehder (
<bibRefCitation author="Nieves-Aldrey, J. L. &amp; Butterill, P. T." pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="221 - 234" refId="ref49437" refString="Nieves-Aldrey, J. L. &amp; Butterill, P. T. (2014) First evidence of cynipids from the Oceanian Region: the description of Lithonecrus papuanus a new genus and species of cynipid inquiline from Papua New Guinea (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae, Synergini). Zootaxa, 3846 (2), 221 - 234. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3846.2.3" type="journal article" year="2014">Nieves-Aldrey &amp; Butterill 2014</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The gall inducers have yet to be confirmed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
